“During the month, the state’s economy added 12,100 jobs — more than double an average pre-pandemic March — with the hottest hiring in tech, corporate and health care positions.

The number of unemployed Georgians is now at its lowest level since June 2001.” https://t.co/NKtRv22L9z

Josh Brown makes an excellent point about Twitter, the bigger a Twitter account gets the more it becomes an existential threat to your real life (old tweets, cancellable takes, etc) so people at a certain level stop using at that point. This checks out to me
